<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\06_stronghold\06_cv_maerwald</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>132</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>A large, liver-spotted man, barrel-chested and paunchy, cowers in the far corner of the room, his white hair a tangled, stringy mess. He covers his face and chest with trembling hands, unable to look in your direction.

"No! Keep away from us! Leave us!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are you Maerwald?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll leave you be, then."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>All at once, he stops shaking, a sudden calmness falling over him. His head tilts forward slightly, and he looks you dead in the eye, like a cornered animal about to pounce. His voice turns suddenly raspy.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm a Watcher. I met a woman in Gilded Vale who thought you could help me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I won't leave until I've spoken to Maerwald."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm no spirit. Do I look like any spirit you have ever seen?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Please. There is something wrong with me. I need Maerwald's help."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You better start making some sense right now or you'll get worse than any spirit could give."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>The old man turns his body away and has another muttered, sputtering argument, facing the wall.

When he turns back toward you, he has taken a confident stance, and his chest is puffed out like a soldier's. A new strength enters his voice. "Maerwald will speak with you. But you will maintain your distance or you'll have me to answer to."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>The man's posture folds, and the hands he'd held strongly at his sides a moment ago resume their original tremors. His voice is feeble and tentative.

"Come to speak to Maerwald? Maerwald whose touch is poison? Maerwald who knows not his effect?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I was told I am a Watcher, and that you could tell me more about it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>He looks up over his hand, the muscles around his eyes twitching, and begins whispering to himself in sharp hisses, as though having an argument.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You seem to have lost your mind."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I was accosted by spirits on my way here. What do they want?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>He nods, still half-distracted, eyeing the door behind you. "A window. Window to the ether, where spirits dwell. Peer and reach into it, speak and listen through it. 

"A Watcher sees souls. Reads them. Knows their pasts. Souls of the living, souls of the dead. An empath." He exhales feebly, his breath wheezing. "And the souls see them back.

"Used it to help beings in both realms, did I. What the gods wanted of me, thought I."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>With a quick spasm, his shoulders straighten and his voice becomes strong. "The gods put me in the world for vengeance, and I obliged."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>He tilts his head forward, glowering at you, and his voice is raspy. "It was the gods' wishes that we protect those lands. My way was the only way to remove the foreigners!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>He shrinks down, and is himself once more. He cradles his face in shaking hands. "Little I knew."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Lost? No. Found more of it. Too much. Too much to bear.

"An Awakening."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You mean you remember your past lives."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's an Awakening?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>He nods. "Something reminds. Memories stirred. Memories before birth. Other bodies, other times."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Many lifetimes we have. Souls enter womb and exit corpse. Carry with them all experiences, all knowledge, all identities.

"Yet we do not remember. Hidden from us. What end? What end? Only the gods know.

"Certain things can stir memories from lives long buried. Awaken the old memories, the old personalities."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Memory, personality, identity, any might resurface."

He looks again at the door behind you. "Or all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald staggers backward, staring off at some imagined phantom. "No. NO! Forgive me! Forgive me."

He covers his mouth with his hand, his breaths convulsing, his eyes red and exhausted.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The spirits I passed - what are they?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Spirits... and not spirits. Always whispering to Maerwald. Reminding him of his mistakes. No sleep.

"Watchers see memories before them - form them from the essence of their own souls.

"Once Maerwald Awakened, he could not make them leave. Gave them more form, not less."
</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 29</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText>"These spirits... they are his own.

"He has lived and relived a thousand painful memories... dealing pain in one life only to feel it in the next."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>Aloth's eyes narrow as he looks at the old man. "How could a... simple Awakening have driven you to this?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The spirits are memories from previous lives?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>He nods, a piteous look on his face. "Troubled memories. Angry memories. Pulling Maerwald back. Reminding him his mistakes.

"Marauder and soldier, soldier and marauder. How could they know?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why do these past lives still trouble you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've seen apparitions like those elsewhere - since I became a Watcher."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>"How do you tell a spirit from a memory?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Fragmented are memories. Stuck in time, mindless, cruel, never far."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>Tears well in Maerwald's eyes. "Oh no. No no. You too? You too."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>Tears well in Maerwald's eyes. "Oh no. No no. You too? You too."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>Aloth's eyes dart between you and Maerwald. "What exactly does he mean? Surely something can be done."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I knew there was something off about you when I met you. But this... this sounds serious."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Told you a Watcher's not to be trusted. What's to be expected when one makes a habit of seeing what's not meant for mortal eyes, if not madness?

"Looks as though our journey together may be a short one."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A mind cannot withstand a sustained attack... least of all against itself. This one has suffered for generations..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What, an inevitable madness? That can't be right." Kana folds his arms. "There's always an answer to be found, if you look hard enough." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 47</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"They will take you too."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"There must be some way to make these memories go away."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My fault. All my fault. Soldier and marauder. Soldier and marauder and Maerwald. No forgiveness for what's past. No undoing what's done."

He looks at you, baggy-eyed and lost. "No sleep. No sleep for the Watcher."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"War there was, all around. War of stone. War of tree."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"War of tree... Oh, of course - the Broken Stone War, and the War of Black Trees. This was in the early period of Aedyran colonization. Fighting between the Dyrwood colonists and the native Glanfathans, you see. But... that was a long time ago..." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Death we brought to the settler men. We the Nine Claws. Claws of Nine. Worse what we did to the women. For love of the gods. The gods' love. For their love."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>54</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald's voice becomes raspy, and he is somewhere else in place and time, speaking to someone unseen.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald cringes, himself again, watching something he can't bear to see, shaking his head over and over. He wails.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>His voice thins to a cracking whisper. "The boy. The boy. The baby boy. The boy.

"Conceived in the raid. Conceived by force. Vessel for marauder, slain in the raid. Marauder and the boy. Marauder and soldier."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That's enough. I don't want to know anymore."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Keep talking, I'm enjoying this."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>He nods, watery-eyed.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You were a monster. You deserve this, even for a past life."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>61</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Take your time. It's over now. It was long ago. Continue when you're ready."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>62</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Go on."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Terrible things happen in war. Living with what you've done is its own penance."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A baby conceived by the raider? What do you mean it was a vessel for him?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"His soul is marked by flame, and those marks will never heal. His trial has broken him, but better that than to live in weakness."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>"For the soul. Marauder's soul. Same soul, one soul. Boy's soul, marauder's soul. Raised in lies and vengeance. Raised to soldier. Raised for the fire. Born for the fire."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>67</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald straightens up, his voice deep. He speaks to some invisible thing. "You'll get no pity from me. The crimes of the Nine Claws clan in the last war are still unavenged. But the gods are just. They have led me here. In my father's name every one of you will burn."

He looks off to his side, as if at someone else standing nearby. "Light it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>68</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 68</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He's talking about two different wars, fought back-to-back. Long time ago. The Broken Stone War and the War of Black Trees.

"The usual conflicts between locals and settlers getting out of hand, both of 'em. Some folks are still mad about what one side did to the other."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>70</ID>
      <DefaultText>Bank Node 70</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>71</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What, so he came back in his next life to burn his own clan? No wonder he's such a mess now. That'll stain you right down to your soul."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>72</ID>
      <DefaultText>Durance smirks. "Burning his own. And why not, if they had been wicked and earned their punishment?

"He is weak of mind and soul. To see him cower before the flame, that should give you the measure of him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>Aloth looks at the old man in horror. "Baye the Usher's crookt bann."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The child born of violence grew into a man of vengeance... and brought fire upon the clan that had brought him both life and death...

"His soul has returned time and again to the same conflict... licking old wounds and inflicting new ones."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald's shoulders slump. He rocks back and forth, agitated. He mutters to himself, oblivious to your presence.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your soul is given to wickedness. The only question is why the gods don't tear it apart."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see no reason. Just bad luck."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Whatever the reason, I don't think we're meant to know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You speak in riddles I don't have the patience to try and understand."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>He shakes his head bitterly. "How little we know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>82</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No. Always there. Always remembered. Can't forget. Can't unsee."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I didn't just remember. Someone caused this. They wore masks and spoke of books and keys and a queen. There was a man there... he seemed familiar to me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>84</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Memory... source?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>85</ID>
      <DefaultText>"They wore hoods and spoke of books and keys and a queen."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>86</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Keys of lead. Books of burden. Queens that were. Known to me are they, the Leaden Key."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What can you tell me about this Leaden Key?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Who is this queen they pray to?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If the Leaden Key caused my Awakening, could they undo it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Secrets. Secrets and deceptions and schemes. Who knows their answers? Not they. Not they.

"Crossed them before. Hatred of Watchers. Hatred and fear. Much we see, threat to secrets."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>91</ID>
      <DefaultText>The old man is hunched over, his head facing to the side as if expecting to be struck. He shakes uncontrollably.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>There is a change in the air of the keep. What was thick and suffocating feels to you somehow more breathable, as though yielding to a conquering invader.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Repair the rope, binding Maerwald's soul here as an eternal warden.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Sever the rope, allowing Maerwald to pass from the world.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Draw upon the energy of the rope itself, siphoning knowledge from the connection.]</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you know where I might find the Leaden Key?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Woedica, goddess. Crown shattered and body burned. Binder of oaths and grudge holder. Bearer of justice, but whose?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>99</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald's bushy white eyebrows edge upward. He begins muttering to himself. Just as you are about ready to repeat your question, he speaks.

"Many secrets do they keep. Un...awaken? Mayhap. Who else if not they?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>101</ID>
      <DefaultText>"City of defiance. Never far from the queen."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>102</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I need to go so I can search for this man from the Leaden Key."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald nods at you, a look of understanding on his face.

"Sleep well. Sleep well."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>104</ID>
      <DefaultText>Before you turn to exit, he tilts his head forward. His eyes lock with yours, cold and dangerous, his voice gravelly.

"Hold! I know your will, Da√Æ! Your actions were seen. You would sooner betray us to the Aedyr land thieves than take orders from me."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>105</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm leaving."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>106</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're confusing me with someone from a past life."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>107</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't have time for this. I will beat you senseless, old man."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>108</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Take it easy. I'm not going to betray anyone."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>109</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'd sooner do a lot of things than take orders from a lunatic."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>110</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your betrayal is for nothing. Your warnings are lost on these foreigners, and their blood will be Galawain's tribute this night. I have asked the elders for the honor of claiming your head as my first trophy and they have granted it. Beg for the Seeker God to grant you a quick death."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>111</ID>
      <DefaultText>In your mind's eye, the bond seems to you as a frayed rope, ghostly and alive, its frayed ends writhing like tidepool anemones, and you find that if you concentrate on it, you have the ability to manipulate its strands.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>112</ID>
      <DefaultText>Maerwald's body lies inert. You can feel his soul lingering there, uncertain.

There is something unique about this soul in this place. A bond formed in decades of inhabitance and lordship that feels somehow palpable to you, as though even in death, the keep knows its former master, and the former master remembers his keep.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>113</ID>
      <DefaultText>The frayed pieces twist and fuse, and as the bond strengthens, the fibers become metal, and the rope becomes a chain.

You watch as Maerwald's soul recedes into the floor, melding with it, spreading thin across it until it is one with the entire place, a silent guardian.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>114</ID>
      <DefaultText>Strand by strand, the connections fly apart like the overstressed strings of some ethereal instrument. With the tearing of the final string, the rope becomes liquid and dissolves from your awareness.

Maerwald's soul hovers near you, a vortex of strife and discord, but there is something else there beneath it - something like relief. His soul passes through one of the walls and is gone.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>You turn both ends of the rope towards you, bringing them into contact with your essence, and as you do, the fibers turn to copper, and through them an energy is conducted into your being. 

You are traveling downward now, beneath the place you stand, seeing places dank and cobwebbed and malignant, like some untended garden overgrown with flora and overrun with vermin. Below everything, at the very bottom, you glimpse for an instant some being you can't quite make out, presiding over it all with brilliant and terrifying power.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>116</ID>
      <DefaultText>One image remains in your perception. A circular room with a stone table that resembles the sun, in an area guarded by suits of armor that move of their own volition. It is deep, not far from the very bottom. There is a door in that room, invisible to all but the most fastidious of eyes, and beyond it, something shimmering, something powerful...

As the image fades, you find yourself in Caed Nua once more. Maerwald's soul is nowhere to be seen.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>117</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You're saying I'll end up like you."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>118</ID>
      <DefaultText>He pouts, as though holding his mouth closed so that the answer won't escape. At length, he nods.

"So fragile, the Watcher's mind. So real his memories. Once Awakened, how can he sleep?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>119</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Leaden Key? It seems we share an enemy, [Player Name]. Assassins and Watcher-wakers both... They certainly keep busy." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>120</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And I seem to be having a conversation with several of them right now."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>121</ID>
      <DefaultText>He nods, sheepish. "Ghosts of the mind. Maerwald has lost control. Maerwald's body no more. "</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>122</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Your past life raided villages, then?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>123</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I met one of your memory-spirits. There was talk of raiding a village."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>124</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then that was his mother I met in the keep. She told him his father was killed by the raiders."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>125</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Raised for the fire?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>126</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If I'm Awakened to a past life, how would that have happened?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>127</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You were reminded of it. Strong memories, lingering lives, they dwell near the surface. Waiting to be remembered. Waiting to take your mind for their own."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>128</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Maerwald sat at his hearth and watched his fire. Watched the wood burn. Then came the memory of another fire, and burning wood. And screams." His face trembles involuntarily.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>129</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Maybe we should come back later?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>130</ID>
      <DefaultText>"And about a, ah, tablet of some worth, after that. Once you two are finished, of course." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>131</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Maerwald isn't here, and he isn't fooled. He has sent for no callers. Begone, deceiving spirit!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>132</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hold her down. Hedhwr, give this Aedyr bitch an heir that belongs in Eir Glanfath."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>133</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Soldier and marauder. Lies and vengeance and dead villages. All dead, all dead."

He looks at you. "What for? What for?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>134</ID>
      <DefaultText>All at once, in spite of his abject misery, his expression changes to one of utmost sympathy. "Poor man. Poor man."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText>All at once, in spite of his abject misery, his expression changes to one of utmost sympathy. "Poor woman. Poor woman."</FemaleText>
    </Entry>
